        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 6:56PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 655 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
developing over Sugar Grove and south of Adwolf, moving northeast at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sugar Grove...
Mount Rogers National Recreation Area...
Troutdale...
Marion Wytheville...
Atkins...
Thomas Bridge...
and Flatridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
